all his property, on condition of paying 1000 ecus to Me Jean Du guet, lad's full brother. Anne-Marie and 2000 crowns to the Illustrious Seigr Ferdinand del Po: no, son of the Illustrious Seig. Charles Antoine4 del POHo;

1500 écus to Barbara and Catherine Cherabitto, daughters of Sébastien, lad's nephew. Anne-Marie, of which 3,000 and 1,500 crowns, bequeathed as above, the lady Anne-Marie, already appointed universal legatee, must keep the usufruct, and not others, etc., and because, etc.

And he says this is his last will and his last will, which he wants to be valid as a nuncupative will and not signed with his own hand.

He makes the executor of this last testament the Seig. Charles Antoine del POHo, to whom he gives ample authorization, etc.

Done in Rome by my ministry, etc., in the presence of: 1 ° Ill. Me Ioe Antonio Cincio, son of the late Marco, of Tibur;

2 °. ill. Seig. Antonio Gattaio, son of the late Aristotle, Romain;

3 °. Mr. Julio Siracchi, from Parma;

4 °. ill. Me Andrea Camillo, from Sancto-Gemino; 5 ° Me Cesare ... Salusto, by Colle Valentino;

6 °. ill. Me Silvestre Bontempo2, Roman citizen. 7 °. Me Sancte, Florentine notable.

r. Carlo Antonio del Pozzo had married, in 1627, Téodora Costa, niece of the bishop of Savona. Their son, Ferdinand, born in 1630, godson of the Ambassador of Tuscany, succeeded his father in the family commandery in 1661.

2. These seven names have never been mentioned in connection with Poussin. We would assume that these are the names of neighbors who have been kind enough to serve as witnesses. Bontempo's name, Bontemps, could designate a Frenchman, without his immediately stated quality of “Roman citizen”.

