b) Large escutcheon, with a crossed out lion: fol. 85, 86, 149, 150;

c) Coats of arms of various prelates: fol. 5, 8, 10, 11, 15, 152, 185, 186, 214;

d) With fleur-de-lis crown and, in a cartouche: MI: March 1, 1641;

e) Crest of France and Orleans: fol. 3.

III. - Various drawings:

a) The letters AC, crowned: fol. 49, 53, 55, 57;

b) A rhombus, with a crescent and BR: fol. 64, 65; c) A swan seen in profile: fol. 2, 112, 118, 121, 124, 125, 127, 257;

d) A swan on three mountains1, surmounted by a star: fol. 97, 101, 134, 145, 146, 156, 157, 159, 161, i63, 166, 167, 169;

e) A sort of fleur-de-lys: fol. 224, 226, 228;

f) A crowned hunting horn: fol. 44, 46, 52;

g) Various designs of vases and amphorae: fol. 25, 27, 30, 31, 32, 67, 69, 77, 79;

h) A rhombus of balls topped with a fleur-de-lis: fol. 36, 39, 48, 59.

Most watermarks feature letters, whether or not surrounded by ornate rectangles, or placed to the right and left, above or below the designs.

